			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Ok - Heres how you do it. Get 4 Orc Picks and turn them into Guard Valon in the West Commonlands at the Toll Booth. Then, if your faction is good enough and you say what he asks in brackets he gives you a bag. Fill this with 8 Cutthroat Insignia Rings (bought off merchants, players or looted from Dervish Cutthroats) then press combine. Give this bag, back to Guard Valon and he gives you a token. Then, take this token to the Armourer in the upstairs of the Freeport Militia Building and you get a Reserve Militia Tunic. This has crappy stats and looks bright red. This is a good quest for a 13 and under, although i would recommend a Dwarven Ringmail Tunic to a level 13 or under. On the above posts, i would like to know of this 'Purple Ringmail Tunic' and if it even exists.
				</font>
